The '''A32''' is a road in [[Hampshire]], southern [[England]], that links [[Gosport]] and [[Alton, Hampshire|Alton]].  Starting at Gosport, facing [[Portsmouth]], it travels north via [[Fareham]], [[Wickham, Hampshire|Wickham]], [[Droxford]], before joining the [[A31 road]] near Alton. The road is {{convert|29.2|mi}} long from the seafront at Gosport to the [[roundabout]] with the A31 near Alton, and has entirely non-[[primary status]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sabre-roads.org.uk/maps/index.php?view=A32&gr=50.96244,-1.05558&map=OSMap&zoom=5&layer=0|title = Ordnance Survey 1:250,000 map|publisher = [[Ordnance Survey]]|accessdate = 2011-12-20}}</ref>

Despite its non-primary status, the road forms the main access to the town of [[Gosport]].  At rush-hour times, the road is often extremely congested (northbound in the morning rush, southbound in the evenings) as commuters head through central [[Fareham]] from the Gosport peninsula to the [[M27 motorway|M27]].  

The main pinch-point is the {{convert|1|mi|adj=on}} long section of road between the Newgate Lane Flyover (junction B3334) and the Quay Street Roundabout in central [[Fareham]] where traffic delays often cause northbound tailbacks of {{convert|3|mi}} at peak times.  During the evening rush, traffic can at times back up to the [[M27 motorway|M27]] at Junction 11 and along the slow lane (Lane One) of the [[motorway]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fareham.gov.uk/council/departments/planning/ldf/sdafaqs.aspx |title=North of Fareham Strategic Development Area |publisher=Fareham Borough Council |accessdate=2011-12-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111127185542/http://www.fareham.gov.uk/council/departments/planning/ldf/sdafaqs.aspx |archivedate=27 November 2011 }}</ref>

There have for many years been plans to provide a [[light rail]] solution to the traffic problem by utilising the former Gosport to Fareham railway line but this was scrapped in 2005. There are now tentative plans to use the railway line for [[guided bus]] services.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.portsmouth.co.uk/news/transport/buses_for_20m_fareham_and_gosport_anti_congestion_scheme_unveiled_1_3219210|title=Buses for £20m Fareham and Gosport anti-congestion scheme unveiled|publisher=The Portsmouth News|accessdate = 2011-12-20}}</ref>

The A32 is a popular route for motorcyclists, particularly at weekends; the cafe ( now Loomies, formerly a "[[Little Chef]]") where the A272 crosses the A32 at [[West Meon]] has become central meeting place for many groups of riders. The historic site of Fort {{Not a typo|Widley}} to the south is easily accessed from Wickham and is a popular route for motorcyclists.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bike Social's Top Routes!|url=https://www.bennetts.co.uk/bikesocial/news-and-views/features/travel/bike-socials-top-routes|website=Bennetts UK|accessdate=27 February 2017|language=en}}</ref>

