{{Expand Farsi|کوه دخان|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox mountain | name = Mountain of Smoke (جبل الدخان) | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 134 | elevation_ref = <ref name="pb">[http://www.peakbagger.com/peak.aspx?pid=10475 "Jabal ad Dukhan"] on Peakbagger.com Retrieved 24 September 2011</ref> | prominence_m = 134 | prominence_ref = <ref name="pb"/> | map = Bahrain | map_caption = Bahrain | map_size = 250 | listing = [[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] | location = [[Bahrain]] | range = | coordinates = {{coord|26|2|20|N|50|32|35|E|type:mountain_region:BH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
The '''Mountain of Smoke''' ({{lang-ar|جبل الدخان}}, {{transl|ar|'''Jabal ad Dukhan'''}}) is a [[hill]] in the [[Southern Governorate]] of [[Bahrain]]. At {{convert|122|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} above [[mean sea level]], it is the country's highest point. The Mountain of Smoke is named as such because of the [[haze]] which often surrounds it on humid days. A number of [[cave]]s of indeterminate type are in the vicinity of the mountain.<ref>{{cite web | last = Collins | first = Lynn | title = Life Before the Oil Boom: The way it used to be | url= http://www.bahrainguide.org/BG1/beforeoil1.html | accessdate = 2008-09-15}} (Archived by the [[Internet Archive]] [https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://www.bahrainguide.org/BG1/beforeoil1.html here], archived by [[WebCite]] [https://www.webcitation.org/5aqVIL6x1 here], Google cache entry [http://www.google.com/search?q=cache:www.bahrainguide.org/BG1/beforeoil1.html here])</ref>
[[Flint]] dating to the [[Stone Age]] have been found on and around the hill.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Rice|first1=Michael|title=The Archaeology of the Arabian Gulf|date=2002|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781134967933|page=149|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0maIAgAAQBAJ&lpg=PA149&dq=bahrain%20%20mountain&pg=PA149#v=onepage|accessdate=17 August 2015}}</ref>
== See also == * [[Geography of Bahrain]] * [[List of tourist attractions in Bahrain]]
