 |image2 = Colonisation2.gif

 |footer = Replica of the [[Iberian Peninsula|Iberian]] ''[[Santa María (ship)|Santa María]]'', the [[Italic people|Italian]] [[Genoese colonies|merchant]] [[navigator]] Christopher Columbus's flagship during his first voyage, a large [[Carvel (boat building)|carvel-built]] ocean-going ship, financed by [[Catholic Monarchs]] of Castile and Aragon.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanderkrogt.net/statues/object.php?webpage=CO&record=es098|title=Columbus Monuments Pages: Valladolid|accessdate=3 January 2010}}</ref> Colombus had estimated a travel distance of {{convert|2400|mi|km|-1}}, far too low.<ref name="Morison-Admiral">[[Samuel Eliot Morison]], ''Admiral of the Ocean Sea: The Life of Christopher Columbus'', (Boston: Atlantic-Little, Brown, 1942). Reissued by the Morison Press, 2007. {{ISBN|1-4067-5027-1}}
